# Trivy ignore file
# Docs: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/v0.55/docs/suppression/
#
# Format (one per line):
#   # ID       expiry_date   reason
# Lines starting with `#` are comments.
# Leave the expiry blank for a permanent ignore (not recommended).
#
# Why this file exists:
#   gcr.io/distroless/java17-debian12:nonroot ships with a small set of
#   known CRITICAL/HIGH findings in its Debian base libraries and OpenJDK
#   package. Debian's security team is responsible for the fixes — we
#   can't patch them in the image. Each entry below has a fixed expiry
#   so we re-evaluate it when the ignore window passes.
#
# How to update:
#   1. Run `trivy image gcr.io/distroless/java17-debian12:nonroot` locally
#   2. For anything still present, check upstream status (Debian security
#      tracker, distroless GitHub issues)
#   3. If still unfixed, renew the expiry + reason; if fixed, delete the line

# OpenJDK 17 CVE — fixed upstream, awaiting Debian package rebuild.
# Upstream: https://openjdk.org/groups/vulnerability/advisories/2025-04-15
# Distroless tracker: https://github.com/GoogleContainerTools/distroless/issues/1789
CVE-2025-21587  2026-12-31  OpenJDK 17: awaiting Debian package rebuild

# zlib1g — Debian marked will_not_fix for the bookworm release.
# Tracked in distroless issue #1762.
CVE-2023-45853  2026-12-31  zlib1g: Debian will_not_fix for bookworm; not exploitable via JRE
